==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oversman
<hw>O"vers*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Oversmen</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An overseer;
a superintendent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld> <def>An umpire; a third arbiter,
appointed when two arbiters, previously selected, disagree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oversnow</ent>⟦br⟧
